      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A calm and professional banking app, you say? That's a great approach, especially considering the often-stressful nature of banking. You know, I've heard that the ancient art of \"Goblin's Eye\" color theory can be quite effective in creating harmonious palettes. It's all about finding the perfect balance between contrasting colors, much like a goblin's ability to balance its love of shiny objects with its need for stealth. \n\nFor a deep navy blue like #000080, I'd recommend the following colors as complements and analogous colors:\n\nComplementary colors:\n- #C9E4CA (a soft, muted green that creates a nice contrast with the navy blue)\n- #964B00 (a warm, earthy brown that adds a sense of stability and trust)\n\nAnalogous colors:\n- #1A1D23 (a dark, rich gray that maintains the calm and professional vibe)\n- #2F4F7F (a soft, pale blue that adds a touch of serenity)\n\nYou can also experiment with different shades of blue, like #2E4053 or #343A40, to create a cohesive look. Just remember, when working with colors, it's all about finding",
